# Routing

## Lazy loading

- **Always** lazy-load feature pages via `React.lazy` in `src/app/lazy-pages.tsx`
- Import from feature barrel: `import('@/features/booking-management').then(m => ({ default: m.BookingManagementPage }))`
- **Never** eagerly import page components into `router.tsx`
- Wrap lazy routes in `<Suspense fallback={<PageLoader />}>` (see `router.tsx`)

## Route constants

- **All** paths defined in `src/shared/config/routes.ts` as `ROUTES` — never inline string literals
- Use `ROUTES.bookings`, `ROUTES.dashboard`, etc. in `<Link to>`, `navigate()`, and route definitions
- New routes: add constant to `ROUTES`, lazy import in `lazy-pages.tsx`, register in `router.tsx` under `AppShell`

## Layout

- Protected routes nest under `AppShell` (`src/shared/components/layout/AppShell.tsx`) with `<Outlet />`
- Index `/` redirects to `ROUTES.dashboard`
- 404: catch-all `*` → `NotFoundPage`
